with%20both%20your%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses%2C%20and%20it's%20accepting%20the%20other%20person%20in%20their%20totality%20with%20their%20unique%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20that%20mindset%2C%20you%20won%E2%80%99t%20go%20into%20fights%20trying%20to%20%E2%80%9Cwin%E2%80%9D%20or%20change%20the%20other%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Change%20how%20you%20listen%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20smiling%20at%20his%20wife%20as%20they%20both%20sit%20outside%20reading%20newspapers%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cba2916fcb546d2d4f1f39%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EPeyton%20Fulford%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERichard%20said%20the%20way%20he%20listens%20to%20clients%20is%20something%20he%20and%20Beverly%20also%20apply%20to%20their%20own%20marriage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt's%20really%20listening%20with%20an%20empathetic%20ear%2C%E2%80%9D%20Beverly%20said%20of%20their%20psychology%20training.%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20having%20that%20ability%20early%20on%20in%20our%20relationship%20has%20really%20made%20a%20big%20difference.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20one%20of%20the%20key%20ways%20to%20become%20a%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Factive-listening%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eactive%20listener%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20to%20reflect%20back%20what%20the%20other%20person%20said%20in%20your%20own%20words.%20%E2%80%9CLetting%20the%20other%20person%20know%20what%20you've%20heard%2C%20that%20you've%20really%20heard%20it%20and%20understood%20it%20is%20really%20the%20first%20step%20in%20resolving%20conflicts%20and%20disagreements%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Pride%20yourself%20on%20flexibility%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20navigating%20conflict%2C%20Beverly%20said%20her%20and%20Richard%E2%80%99s%20other%20strengths%20are%20their%20flexible%20mindsets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20very%20quickly%20can%20not%20only%20see%20the%20other%20person's%20point%20of%20view%2C%20our%20partner's%20point%20of%20view%2C%20but%20we%20also%20can%20incorporate%20it%20and%20see%20how%20it%20might%20fit%20into%20a%20common%20goal%20rather%20than%20just%20digging%20our%20heels%20in%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20skill%20often%20naturally%20leads%20to%20reaching%20a%20middle%20ground%2C%20because%20both%20participants%20are%20already%20considering%20the%20other%20person%E2%80%99s%20needs%20and%20perspective.%20%E2%80%9CObviously%2C%20we%20don't%20always%20agree%20on%20everything%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbut%20I%20think%20because%20we%20do%20listen%20to%20each%20other%2C%20we%20can%20understand%20that%20person's%20point%20of%20view%20and%20we%20can%20almost%20invariably%20reach%20a%20compromise.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Mimic%20your%20therapist%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERichard%20said%20that%20both%20he%20and%20Beverly%20were%20brought%20up%20in%20homes%20where%20empathy%20and%20caring%20for%20other%20people%20were%20considered%20important%20values.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20you%20were%20raised%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femotionally-immature-parent-signs-psychologist-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eemotionally%20immature%20parents%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20good%20model%20of%20healthy%20relationships%2C%20going%20to%20therapy%20can%20do%20two%20things%3A%20help%20you%20unpack%20your%20past%20and%20also%20indirectly%20learn%20what%20respectful%20communication%20looks%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeverly%20said%20that%20a%20good%20therapist%20will%20be%20modeling%20empathy%20as%20they%20talk%20to%20you.%20Beyond%20their%20client%20opening%20up%20more%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthey%20begin%20to%20learn%20not%20by%20being%20taught%2C%20but%20more%20just%20by%20example%20and%20how%20that%20makes%20them%20feel%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20They%20can%20feel%20themselves%20become%20more%20vulnerable%20when%20they%20feel%20heard%20and%20safe%2C%20and%20start%20to%20mimic%20that%20in%20their%20own%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Dig%20deeper%20into%20stalemates%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeverly%20said%20one%20of%20the%20most%20common%20things%20people%20fight%20about%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freasons-why-people-break-up-couples-split-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esplit%20up%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%2C%20are%20money%2C%20sex%2C%20and%20child-rearing%20%E2%80%94%20topics%20that%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20see%20a%20compromise%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20see%20the%20middle%20ground%20%3Cstrong%3Ebecause%20the%20conflict%20is%20too%20steeped%20in%20history%20and%20emotion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20she%20%3Cstrong%3Erecommended%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Egoing%20in%20multiple%20rounds%20of%20%3Cstrong%3Ehearing%20and%20repeating%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20what%20the%20other%20person%20said.%20After%20that%2C%20she%20said%20the%20couple%20should%20ask%20themselves%20what%20their%20common%20goal%20is%20and%20if%20they%E2%80%99ve%20explored%20every%20alternative%20there%20is%20to%20reaching%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20the%20surface-level%20issue%20is%20over%20how%20to%20raise%20their%20child%2C%20the%20core%20could%20be%20both%20parents%20wanting%20their%20kid%20to%20be%20self-sufficient%20as%20an%20adult.%20They%20can%20then%20look%20at%20both%20proposed%20solutions%20and%20see%20if%20either%20fits%20that%20goal%20%E2%80%94%20or%20look%20for%20completely%20new%20ways%20to%20reach%20that%20goal%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20this%20is%20easier%20said%20than%20done%2C%20Richard%20emphasized%20that%20couple%E2%80%99s%20therapy%20can%20especially%20help%20with%20these%20sorts%20of%20problems.%20%E2%80%9CHaving%20a%20couple%20listen%20to%20each%20other%2C%20being%20able%20to%20really%20hear%20each%20other%20in%20a%20therapeutic%20setting%20with%20a%20third%20party%20%E2%80%93%20that%20seems%20to%20be%20an%20opportunity%20to%20do%20that%20in%20a%20way%20that%20they%20can't%20accomplish%20at%20home%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20Take%20a%20walk%20together%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20Beverly%20said%20she%20always%20recommends%20taking%20a%20breath%20before%20responding%20in%20the%20heat%20of%20the%20moment%20so%20as%20to%20avoid%20knee-jerk%20reactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20that%20same%20vein%2C%20she%20also%20suggested%20taking%20regular%20walks%20with%20your%20partner%2C%20as%20the%20physical%20movement%20can%20aid%20in%20conflict%20prevention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThings%20slip%20out%20when%20you're%20talking%20with%20each%20other%20and%20walking%2C%20and%20those%20things%20that%20slip%20out%20can%20often%20help%20the%20conflict%20even%20before%20you%20get%20into%20a%20heated%20disagreement%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20Rather%20than%20stewing%2C%20you%20might%20bring%20up%20an%20issue%20you%20didn%E2%80%99t%20realize%20was%20bothering%20you%20%E2%80%94%20and%20resolve%20it%20on%20the%20walk%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20already%20in%20the%20thick%20of%20a%20fight%2C%20she%20said%20walking%20and%20taking%20some%20deeper%20breaths%20can%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20calmly%20share%20your%20thoughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMost%20people%20can%20do%20it%2C%20even%20people%20our%20age%2C%20and%20it%20gets%20you%20out%20in%20nature%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20change%20in%20the%20environment%20itself%2C%20the%20physical%20activity%20together%20%E2%80%94%20you%20get%20rid%20of%20some%20of%20the%20tension%20that%20you%20were%20holding%20when%20you're%20angry.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-stop-having-the-same-couples-fight-over-and-over-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707909601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cba23ef533b039a882f9e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-stop-having-the-same-couples-fight-over-and-over-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dr.%20Beverly%20Palmer%20and%20Dr.%20Richard%20C.%20Palmer%20have%20been%20married%20for%2056%20years.%20They%20shared%20their%20best%20advice%20for%20navigating%20relationship%20conflicts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpugachevsky%40insider.com%20(Julia%20Pugachevsky)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-stop-having-the-same-couples-fight-over-and-over-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%227%20sex%20tips%20from%20a%20couple%20married%20for%2042%20years%20%E2%80%94%20including%20a%20lingerie%20budget%20and%20non-sexual%20intimacy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222249%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rita%20and%20Theodore%20kissing%20on%20the%20couch%20with%20%26quot%3BThe%20Creation%20of%20Adam%26quot%3B%20behind%20them%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c5443e43bb77284ba51c0e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBryan%20Tarnowski%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERita%20Smith%2C%2062%2C%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20Theodore%20Smith%2C%20Sr.%2C%2064%2C%20have%20been%20married%20for%20over%2040%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20shared%20their%20best%20sex%20tips%2C%20from%20investing%20in%20lingerie%20to%20bonding%20outside%20the%20bedroom.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFor%20more%20advice%20from%20forever-cou