20these%20two%20years%2C%20she%20lived%20in%20a%20domestic%20violence%20shelter%20and%20a%20shelter%20for%20low-income%20residents%2C%20as%20she%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20afford%20an%20apartment%20and%20the%20costs%20of%20raising%20a%20kid.%20Because%20of%20her%20income%2C%20she%20said%20she%20qualified%20for%20day%20care%20for%20her%20son%2C%20though%20money%20was%20still%20tight.%20She%20drove%20while%20her%20son%20was%20in%20daycare%2C%20typically%20between%206%20a.m.%20and%206%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20flexible%20for%20me%20since%20I%20could%20pick%20my%20own%20hours%20and%20be%20my%20own%20boss%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jayla%20said.%20%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20listen%20to%20someone%20telling%20me%20to%20go%20take%20a%20break.%20It%20worked%20out%20for%20me.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20two%20years%2C%20she%20maintained%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-uber-drivers-make-fulltime-cancelling-rides-gig-economy-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efive-star%20rating%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20speaking%20to%20all%20her%20riders%20and%20doing%20small%20favors%20for%20customers%20like%20adding%20a%20stop.%20She%20said%20maintaining%20a%20high%20rating%20came%20with%20benefits%20from%20the%20ride-hailing%20companies%2C%20such%20as%20new%20tires%20or%20oil%20changes%2C%20though%20she%20said%20it%20was%20difficult%20to%20redeem%20these.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20started%20having%20problems%20with%20her%20car%2C%20it%20was%20difficult%20for%20her%20to%20keep%20paying%20all%20her%20car%20maintenance%20bills%2C%20so%20she%20applied%20for%20Lyft%20Express%20Drive%2C%20Lyft%E2%80%99s%20rental%20program%20through%20Hertz%20and%20Flexdrive.%20She%20was%20put%20on%20a%20waitlist%20and%20never%20heard%20back%2C%20and%20Jayla%20decided%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20worth%20it%20to%20continue%20waiting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20profile%20says%20five%20stars%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20years%20and%20