C%20North%20Dakota%2C%20Ohio%2C%20South%20Dakota%2C%20and%20Wisconsin.%C2%A0And%2C%20of%20the%20545%2C598%20people%20who%20left%20New%20York%20last%20year%2C%2041%2C730%20headed%20to%20the%20Midwest.%20Some%20are%20bringing%20their%20coastal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-cost-of-living-nyc-kansas-city-midwest-rent-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esalaries%20with%20them.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20some%20of%20those%20movers%20are%20ready%20to%20mingle%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finstitute.bankofamerica.com%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Fbank-of-america-institute%2Feconomic-insights%2Fon-the-move-west-side-story.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAccording%20to%20a%20Bank%20of%20America%20analysis%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20over%2090%25%20of%202023%20movers%20into%20St.%20Louis%2C%20the%20home%20of%20Hatch%E2%80%99d%2C%20are%20single-person%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20influx%20of%20singles%20isn't%20purely%20a%20perk%20for%20locals.%20Matt%20R.%2C%20a%20senior%20at%20Indiana%20University%20who%20dates%20both%20men%20and%20women%2C%20has%20seen%20firsthand%20the%20divide%20between%20locals%20and%20the%20educated%20young%20professionals%20and%20students%20flocking%20into%20the%20area%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rentcafe.com%2Faverage-rent-market-trends%2Fus%2Fin%2Fbloomington%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehousing%20costs%20skyrocketing%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere's%20almost%20a%20class%20divide%20in%20dating%20between%20young%20professionals%20or%20students%20and%20then%20people%20that%20are%20the%20same%20age%20but%20maybe%20don't%20have%20a%20college%20degree%20and%20just%20work%20somewhere%20in%20town%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20Matt%20chalks%20that%20up%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20%E2%80%9Cpeople%20want%20to%20date%20people%20like%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20thinks%20that%20those%20students%20and%20young%20professionals%20might%20feel%20less%20inclined%20to%20pursue%20someone%20in%20blue%3Cstrong%3E-%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecollar%20work%2C%20and%20would%20rather%20date%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20future%20of%20Midwest%20dating%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20hope%20this%20can%20change%2C%20but%20I%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20in%20a%20lower%20tax%20bracket%20might%20just%20move%20elsewhere%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20There%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cdefinitely%20the%20problem%20of%20these%20young%20professionals%20kind%20of%20pushing%20locals%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20shift%20in%20the%20dating%20mindset%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20yearning%20to%20find%20love%2C%20according%20to%20Courtney%20Quinlan%2C%20CEO%20and%20matchmaker%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmidwestmatchmaking.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMidwest%20Matchmaking%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20agency%20mainly%20services%20the%20Dakotas%2C%20the%20Twin%20Cities%2C%20Chicago%2C%20Nebraska%2C%20Iowa%2C%20Kansas%2C%20and%20Missouri.%20While%20business%20is%20usually%20always%20booming%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20booming%20even%20more%20now%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20She%E2%80%99s%20also%20getting%20more%20calls%20than%20ever%20from%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecommunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe're%20super%20busy%20and%20are%20signing%20up%20people.%20I%20work%20seven%20days%20a%20week%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20never%20get%20a%20day%20off.%20And%20I%20love%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20dating%20priorities%20are%20shifting%2C%20she%20said.%20Gone%20are%20the%20days%20of%20app%20dominance%2C%20especially%20as%20younger%20dates%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2F2023%2F11%2F05%2Fdating-apps-college-students-tinder-bumble%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforsake%20online%20dating%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-dating-trend-online-apps-friends-romantic-partners-relationships-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein-person%20connections.%3C%2Fa%3E%20There's%20also%20a%20shift%20away%20from%20dating%20with%20the%20specific%20aim%20of%20settling%20into%20marriage%20and%20parenthood%20right%20away.%20Instead%2C%20Quinlan%20said%20she's%20noticed%20what%20she%20believes%20is%20a%20more%20coastal%20version%20of%20dating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20think%20there's%20always%20been%20such%20a%20pressure%20in%20society%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20Midwest%2C%20to%20get%20married%2C%20have%20kids%2C%20have%20your%20white%20picket%20fence%2C%20all%20the%20things%2C%E2%80%9D%20Quinlan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20people%20want%20something%20different%3A%20Someone%20who%20they%20love%2C%20%E2%80%9Ctheir%20person%2C%E2%80%9D%20rather%20than%20someone%20who%20just%20checks%20their%20boxes%20for%20a%20spouse.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt's%20a%20more%20romanticized%2C%20less%20utilitarian%20view%20on%20partnering%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20also%20getting%20back%20to%20the%20basics.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20that%20are%20really%20serious%20about%20dating%20are%20sick%20of%20using%20all%20the%20technology%2C%20like%20the%20constant%20swiping%2C%20the%20constant%20videos%2C%20the%20constant%20texting%2C%20all%20of%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Quinlan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20predicts%20that%20the%20next%20dating%20generation%20%E2%80%94%20those%20who%20are%20seeking%20out%20that%20just-right%20partner%2C%20as%20Midwesterners%20are%20now%20%E2%80%94%20are%20going%20to%20be%20doing%20less%20of%20that%20virtual%20connecting%20and%20%26quot%3Bmore%20actually%20getting%20face-to-face%20meeting%20for%20coffee%2C%20meeting%20at%20the%20dog%20park%2C%26quot%3B%20rather%20%26quot%3Bthen%20hiding%20behind%20their%20cellphone%20and%20their%20apartment%20chatting%20for%20three%20months%20and%20then%20finding%20the%20person%20they%20were%20chatting%20with%20is%20somebody%20totally%20different%20or%20getting%20ghosted%20after%20three%20months.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuinlan%20believes%20the%20shift%20originated%20in%20larger%20coastal%20cities%20and%20migrated%20inland%20along%20with%20pandemic-era%20transplants.%20She%E2%80%99s%20increasingly%20hearing%20that%20desire%20from%20people%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20places%20like%20Kansas%20City%20or%20Sioux%20Falls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEverything%20that%20comes%20from%20the%20bigger%20cities%20and%20the%20coast%2C%20the%20music%2C%20the%20clothes%2C%20everything%20kind%20of%20migrates%20to%20the%20Midwest%2C%20and%20we%20kind%20of%20get%20it%20last%2C%E2%80%9D%20Quinlan%20said.%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20that%20mindset%20and%20that%20culture%20has%20been%20going%20on%20in%20bigger%20cities%20for%20obviously%20longer.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPeople%20want%20to%20connect%2C%20but%20newcomers%20also%20bring%20challenges%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20Americans%2C%20Midwesterners%20%E2%80%94%20both%20new%20and%20old%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20are%20eager%20to%20connect%20right%20now.%20Look%20no%20further%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.popupcommons.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPop-Up%20Commons%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Omaha%2C%20Nebraska.%20Started%20in%202023%2C%20the%20community%20center%20was%20created%20explicitly%20to%20be%20a%20third%20space%20for%20Nebraskans%20to%20congregate%20in%20%E2%80%94%20and%20yes%2C%20perhaps%20to%20date%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe're%20starting%20to%20see%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20gather%20here%20as%20their%20third%20space%20and%20meet%20people%2C%20which%20is%20really%20awesome.%20We've%20been%20able%20to%20connect%20so%20many%20people%20to%20each%20other%2C%E2%80%9D%20Maranda%20Taylor%2C%20one%20of%20the%20space%E2%80%99s%20co-founders%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPop-Up%20Commons%E2%80%99%20old-school%2C%20diner-style%20speed%20dating%20was%20%E2%80%9Cwildly%20successful%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20Taylor%2C%20and%20a%20ladies'%20night%20event%20devoted%20to%20talking%20about%20taboo%20topics%2C%20including%20sex%2C%20sold%20out%20before%20ticket%20sales%20even%20closed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20pandemic%2C%20everybody%E2%80%99s%20been%20lonely%2C%20Taylor%20said.%20They%E2%80%99re%20searching%20for%20connections%20and%20that%20third%20space%20outside%20work%20and%20home.%20That%20includes%20newcomers%2C%20who%20find%20the%20space%20on%20Google%20and%20come%20in%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20most%20part%2C%20it%20is%20a%20good%20mix%20of%20all%20sorts%20of%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20mix%20of%20people%20also%20means%20that%20Quinlan%2C%20the%20matchmaker%2C%20has%20noticed%20that%20politics%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20big%20divider%20among%20prospective%20daters.%20During%20her%2018%20years%20as%20a%20matchmaker%2C%20she%20never%20had%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20ask%20people%20about%20their%20political%20affiliations.%20But%20over%20the%20past%20eight%20years%20%E2%80%94%20and%20especially%20during%20the%20thick%20of%20the%20pandemic%20%E2%80%94%20it%E2%80%99s%20become%20something%20they%E2%80%99ve%20absolutely%20had%20to%20ask.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20completely%20changed%20the%20way%20we%20did%20matching%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20could%20have%20a%20really%20great%20match%20at%20one%20point%20that%20we%20would've%20matched%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20there's%20no%20way%20in%20hell%20we%20would've%20matched%20'em%20when%20the%20views%20had%20completely%20changed%20when%20politics%20were%20involved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20the%20polarization%20has%20calmed%20a%20bit%2C%20with%20people%20willing%20to%20match%20with%20others%20who%20may%20not%20see%20eye%20to%20eye%2C%20but%20aren%E2%80%99t%20extreme%20in%20their%20views%2C%20Quinlan%20said.%20Indeed%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%