20kitchen%2C%20and%20a%20bedroom%20downstairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202003%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20add%20an%20ADU%20to%20my%20home.%20I%20was%20a%20single%20parent%20and%20retiring%2C%20so%20I%20knew%20that%20my%20income%20stream%20would%20be%20different.%20I%20thought%20that%20renting%20out%20the%20ADU%20would%20be%20economical%2C%20and%20maybe%20there%20was%20a%20possibility%20that%20my%20mother%20or%20another%20family%20member%20would%20eventually%20want%20to%20live%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20there%20were%20no%20programs%20available%20for%20assistance.%20Now%2C%20however%2C%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-city-funding-adu-tiny-homehousing-shortage-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enew%20laws%20to%20help%20homeowners%20finance%20construction%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20jealous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20then%2C%20I%20remortgaged%20my%20house%20and%20took%20out%20some%20extra%20money%20to%20renovate%20and%20build%20the%20ADU.%20In%20all%2C%20I%20spent%20about%20%2425%2C000%20on%20construction.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20I%E2%80%99ve%20had%20only%20three%20tenants.%20Their%20rent%20has%20helped%20me%20almost%20pay%20off%20my%2030-year%20mortgage%2C%20and%20has%20covered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-property-taxes-every-us-state%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproperty%20taxes%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-escrow%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eescrow%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20rent%20does%20not%20increase%20like%20inflation%2C%20it%20has%20been%20very%20helpful%20in%20alleviating%20worries%20about%20paying%20bills%2C%20and%20has%20given%20me%20extra%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20had%20to%20ask%20my%20neighbors%20for%20approval%20to%20build%20an%20ADU%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20home