Fsupreme-court-bilkis-bano-gujarat-government-review-petition-remarks-expunged-249410%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20ruled%20that%20the%20order%20had%20been%20obtained%20by%20Radheshyam%20Shah%2C%20one%20of%20the%20convicts%2C%20by%20playing%20fraud%20on%20the%20court%20and%20misrepresenting%20or%20suppressing%20material%20facts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20was%20referring%20to%20an%20earlier%20ruling%20delivered%20by%20Justice%20Ajay%20Rastogi%20(now%20retired)%20on%20May%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbilkis-bano-convicts-fraud-gujarat-government%5C%22%3EBilkis%20Bano%20Convicts%3A%20Who%20Is%20Accountable%20for%20the%20%E2%80%98Fraud%E2%80%99%20by%20Gujarat%20Government%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20writ%20petition%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20in%20May%202022%20held%20State%20of%20Gujarat%20to%20be%20the%20appropriate%20government%20for%20considering%20the%20remission%20plea.%20Following%20this%20May%202022%20order%2C%20a%20series%20of%20developments%20took%20place%20which%20resulted%20in%20the%20release%20of%20all%2011%20life%20convicts%20in%20the%20Bilkis%20Bano%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%208%2C%20the%20court%20noted%20that%20the%20convicts%E2%80%99%20release%20had%20been%20ordered%20based%20on%20Gujarat%E2%80%99s%201992%20remission%20policy%2C%20which%20had%20been%20superseded%20by%20a%202014%20law%2C%20and%20ordered%20the%2011%20convicts%20to%20surrender%20within%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202002%2C%20Bilkis%20Bano%20was%2021%20years%20old%20and%20pregnant%20when%20she%20was%20gang-raped%20during%20the%20Gujarat%20riots%3B%207%20members%20of%20her%20family%2C%20including%20her%20three-year-old%20daughter%20was%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707894617000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F05%2Fbilkis-bano-with-her-husband-and-daughter.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbilkis-bano-case-gujarat-government-moves-sc-wants-adverse-comments-dropped%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20its%20appeal%2C%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20stated%20that%20the%20comments%20in%20the%20judgement%20related%20to%20the%20case%20were%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20only%20highly%20unwarranted%20and%20against%20the%20record%20of%20the%20case%2C%20but%20has%20caused%20serious%20prejudice%20to%20the%20State%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbilkis-bano-case-gujarat-government-moves-sc-wants-adverse-comments-dropped%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mother%20appears%20in%20court%20charged%20with%20murder%20of%20six-year-old%20son%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707894540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F02%2F768x432%2Fskynews-matthew-healy-ireland_6455199.jpg%3F20240214110027%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fruth-purcell-healy-mother-appears-in-court-charged-with-murder-of-six-year-old-son-13071269%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20woman%20has%20appeared%20in%20court%20in%20Ireland%20charged%20with%20the%20murder%20of%20her%20six-year-old%20son.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A64%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fruth-purcell-healy-mother-appears-in-court-charged-with-murder-of-six-year-old-son-13071269%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fruth-purcell-healy-mother-appears-in-court-charged-with-murder-of-six-year-old-son-13071269%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fruth-purcell-healy-mother-appears-in-court-charged-with-murder-of-six-year-old-son-13071269%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Refuses%20to%20Stay%20Section%20of%20Law%20Allowing%20PM-Led%20Panel%20to%20Appoint%20Election%20Commissioners%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20refused%20to%20stay%20a%20section%20under%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20the%20Other%20Election%20Commissioners%20Act%2C%202023%2C%20as%20per%20which%20a%20selection%20committee%20headed%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20a%20Union%20minister%20and%20the%20leader%20of%20opposition%20would%20appoint%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20(CEC)%20and%20other%20election%20commissioners%20(ECs).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20section%207%20of%20the%20Act%2C%20the%20President%20would%20appoint%20the%20CEC%20and%20the%20ECs%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20a%20selection%20committee%20comprising%20the%20prime%20minister%20as%20its%20chairperson%2C%20a%20union%20cabinet%20minister%20nominated%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20and%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20as%20its%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20section%20goes%20against%20a%20judgment%20by%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20apex%20court%20in%20March%202022%20which%20had%20disapproved%20of%20the%20system%20brought%20in%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20suggested%20that%20the%20selection%20committee%20includes%20the%20PM%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20Opposition%20and%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%20(CJI).%20It%20was%20aimed%20at%20insulating%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day%20to%20influence%20appointment%20of%20top%20officials%20who%20conduct%20elections%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20on%20February%2013%2C%20a%20two-member%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20hearing%20a%20fresh%20petition%20challenging%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%20refused%20to%20stay%20the%20operation%20of%20the%20law.%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20and%20Dipankar%20Datta%2C%20responding%20to%20the%20plea%20filed%20by%20the%20NGO%2C%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%2C%20issued%20a%20notice%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20listed%20the%20next%20hearing%20of%20the%20case%20in%20April%20along%20with%20the%20other%20petitions%20on%20the%20same%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppearing%20for%20ADR%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Prashant%20Bhushan%20argued%20that%20the%20section%20is%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20ruling%20of%20the%20five-judge%20bench.%20Since%20two%20ECs%20are%20about%20to%20retire%2C%20if%20the%20operation%20of%20the%20law%20is%20not%20stayed%2C%20the%20plea%20would%20become%20infructuous.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Justice%20Khanna%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fsupreme-court-refuses-to-stay-law-on-appointment-of-cec-ecs%2Farticleshow%2F107670602.cms%5C%22%3Estated%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20matter%20which%20can%20be%20decided%20like%20this.%20A%20legislation%20of%20Parliament%20cannot%20be%20stayed%20like%20this.%20We%20have%20to%20examine%20the%20issue%20in%20terms%20of%20power%20of%20judicial%20review.%20We%20will%20hear%20this%20petition%20along%20with%20other%20pending%20petitions%20on%20the%20issue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%2012%2C%20hearing%20a%20petition%20filed%20by%20a%20Congress%20member%20Jaya%20Thakur%20which%20said%20section%207%20and%208%20of%20the%20Act%20did%20not%20provide%20an%20independent%20mechanism%20to%20appoint%20the%20CEC%20and%20the%20ECs%2C%20the%20court%20had%20also%20refused%20to%20stay%20the%20law%20but%20had%20issued%20a%20notice%20to%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20cannot%20stay%20a%20statutory%20amendment.%20Issue%20notice%20is%20returnable%20in%20April%202024%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Khanna%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court%2Fstory%2Fsupreme-court-election-commissioners-appointments-new-law-statutory-amend